content:
Omni-Channel is a flexible, customizable feature that lets you configure it declaratively without writing code. Use Omni-Channel to manage the priority of work items and route them to agents quickly. Manage agent capacity and assign different types of work to groups of agents.

Omni-Channel routes work requests to the most available and qualified support agents in the app. You can provide real-time operational intelligence to support supervisors with Omni Supervisor. Agents no longer have to pick and choose work assignments manually, saving time, effort, and brainpower.

Routing logic is applied when work is assigned to an owner. If field values on the work item are changed after the item is routed, the routing logic isn’t reapplied.

Omni-Channel is supported in both Lightning Experience (recommended) and Salesforce Classic. You can run Omni-Channel in both standard and console apps.

Use different ways to route work, including Omni-Channel flows. Set up Omni-Channel to route any type of incoming work item to the most qualified, available support agents. Omni-Channel integrates seamlessly into both console and standard apps.

Test your implementation to make sure it’s working correctly. Manage agents, queues, and skills in Omni Supervisor. Provide customer support for real-time channels with Omni-Channel.
title: Route Work with Service Cloud's Omni-Channel
